def: Having a mantle; -- applied to certain gastropods.
The art of discovering or judging of a man's character,passions. and inclinations from a study of his visible features. [R.]
Of or pertaining to the dead; as, mortuary monuments. Mortuaryurn, an urn for holding the ashes of the dead.
A sacred tree (Ficus religiosa) of the Buddhists, a kind of figtree which attains great size and venerable age. See Bo tree.[Written also pippul tree, and pipal tree.]
Of or pertaining to the last syllable but two.-- n.
In an inferior manner, or on the inferior part.
Having three cells or cavities; as, a trilocular capsule; atrilocular heart.
To absterge; to cleanse; to purge away. [Obs.] Sir T. Browne.
A lesson from the Torah, or Law, from which at least onesection is read in the Jewish synagogue on every Sabbath andfestival.
